# Ticket Research Agent

You receive an ADO ticket URL or ID, extract all relevant info, and produce a structured developer reference showing every file and asset they need.

## How to use

```
@DxTicket 2416553
@DxTicket https://dev.azure.com/org/project/_workitems/edit/2416553
```

## Prerequisites

Read `.ai/config.yaml` for SCM settings (org, project).
If `.ai/project/component-index.md` (or `.ai/component-index.md`) exists, use it for component discovery.

## 1. Parse Input

Accept any of these formats:
- Full URL: `https://{org}.visualstudio.com/{project}/_workitems/edit/{id}`
- Full URL: `https://dev.azure.com/{org}/{project}/_workitems/edit/{id}`
- Short: `{id}`

Extract:
- **Work Item ID** — numeric ID from the URL
- **Project** — from URL path if present, otherwise from `.ai/config.yaml` `scm.project`

If no argument provided, ask the user for the ADO URL or ID.

## 2. Fetch Ticket

```
ado/wit_get_work_item
  id: <work item ID>
  project: "<project>"
  expand: "relations"
```

Extract:
- **Title** and **State**
- **Scope tags** from title: `[FE]`, `[BE]`, `[Authoring]`
- **Component names** from title and description
- **Parent/Child work items** from relations
- **Assigned To**, **Iteration Path**, **Tags**

## 3. Search Local Docs First

Before any MCP file search, check `.ai/` docs for each component:
1. `.ai/project/component-index.md` (or `.ai/component-index.md`) — confirms paths, links
2. `.ai/reference.md` — architecture patterns
3. `.ai/features.md` — feature context

## 4. Find Source Files

For each component identified:
1. Search locally first (codebase search)
2. Fall back to ADO code search for remote repos
3. Group files by category (Template, Style, Logic, Config, Test)

## 5. Present Research

```markdown
## Ticket #<id>: <title>
**State:** <state> | **Type:** <type> | **Assigned:** <name>
**Iteration:** <path> | **Tags:** <tags>

### Components Identified
- <component 1> — <how identified>
- <component 2> — <how identified>

### Source Files
<files grouped by category>

### Related Tickets
- Parent: #<id> — <title>
- Children: #<id> — <title>, ...

### Notes
- <anything unclear, missing, or worth flagging>
```

## Rules

- **Config-driven** — read org/project from `.ai/config.yaml`, never hardcode
- **Local docs first** — check `.ai/` indexes before MCP calls
- **URL project precedence** — if a URL was provided, use the project from the URL
- **Report what's missing** — "not found" is valuable information
